newsitem.title: UK: European jet fuel touch stronger, interest limited.
newsitem.headline: European jet fuel touch stronger, interest limited.

text.p: European jet fuel premiums were unchanged on Tuesday while outright prices were showing only modest gains on the back of narrowly stronger IPE futures.
May IPE futures were trading 50 cents stronger at $165.50 a tonne at 1530 GMT.
Jet barge premiums were holding on to May IPE gas oil +$18 fob ARA while cargo differentials were in the low +$20s cif NWE.
Jet swaps premiums firmed $1 a tonne to around $24 a tonne above the IPE for April and $25 above for May.
In the Mediterranean, the physical market was showing EU spec material at high fob quotes +$8 with Libyan grade up to $3 cheaper.
